"Polyakov I.V., Alekseev G.V., Bekryaev R.V., Bhatt U., Colony R.L., Johnson M.A., Karklin V.P., Makshtas A.P., Walsh D., Yulin A.V.","Observationally based assessment of polar amplification of global warming",2002,"Geophysical Research Letters","29","18",,"25","1",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0242501553&partnerID=40&md5=cc616d9e2e8e33c8377c4403c8f7c2fa","International Arctic Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Arctic/Antarctic Research Institute, 38 Bering St., St. Petersburg 199397, Russian Federation; Institute of Marine Science, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States","Polyakov, I.V., International Arctic Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Alekseev, G.V., Arctic/Antarctic Research Institute, 38 Bering St., St. Petersburg 199397, Russian Federation; Bekryaev, R.V., Arctic/Antarctic Research Institute, 38 Bering St., St. Petersburg 199397, Russian Federation; Bhatt, U., International Arctic Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Colony, R.L., International Arctic Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Johnson, M.A., Institute of Marine Science, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Karklin, V.P., Arctic/Antarctic Research Institute, 38 Bering St., St. Petersburg 199397, Russian Federation; Makshtas, A.P., International Arctic Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Walsh, D., International Arctic Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Yulin, A.V., Arctic/Antarctic Research Institute, 38 Bering St., St. Petersburg 199397, Russian Federation","Arctic variability is dominated by multi-decadal fluctuations. Incomplete sampling of these fluctuations results in highly variable arctic surface-air temperature (SAT) trends. Modulated by multi-decadal variability, SAT trends are often amplified relative to northern-hemispheric trends, but over the 125-year record we identify periods when arctic SAT trends were smaller or of opposite sign than northern-hemispheric trends. Arctic and northern-hemispheric air-temperature trends during the 20th century (when multi-decadal variability had little net effect on computed trends) are similar, and do not support the predicted polar amplification of global warming. The possible moderating role of sea ice cannot be conclusively identified with existing data. If long-term trends are accepted as a valid measure of climate change, then the SAT and ice data do not support the proposed polar amplification of global warming. Intrinsic arctic variability obscures long-term changes, limiting our ability to identify complex feedbacks in the arctic climate system.",,"Amplification; Climate change; Thermal effects; Surface-air temperature (SAT); Global warming; air temperature; global warming; polar region; trend analysis",,,,,,"Chapman, W.L., Walsh, J.E., Recent variations of sea ice and air temperature in high latitudes (1993) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 74, pp. 33-47; Delworth, T.L., Mann, M.E., Observed and simulated multidecadal variability in the Northern Hemisphere (2000) Climate Dynamics, 16, pp. 661-676; Doronin, Yu.P., (1971) Thermal Interaction of the Atmosphere and the Hydrosphere in the Arctic, , Philadelphia, Coronet Books, 252 pp; (SAR) climate change 1995 (1996) The Science of Climate Change, Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, pp. 86-103. , IPCC, J. T. Houghton et al., eds., Cambridge U. Press; Jones, P.D., New, M., Parker, D.E., Martin, S., Rigor, I.G., Surface air temperature and its changes over the past 150 years (1999) Review of Geophysics, 37 (2), pp. 173-199; Kahl, J.D., Charlevoix, D.J., Zaitseva, N.A., Schnell, R.C., Serreze, M.C., Absence of evidence for greenhouse warming over the Arctic Ocean in the past 40 years (1993) Nature, 361, pp. 335-337; Martin, S., Minoz, E.A., Drucker, R., Recent observations of a spring-summer surface warming over the Arctic Ocean (1997) Geophys. Res. Lett., 24, pp. 1259-1262; Parkinson, C.L., Cavalieri, D.J., Gloersen, P., Zwally, H.J., Comiso, J.C., Arctic sea ice extents, areas, and trends, 1978-1996 (1999) J. Geophys. Res., 104, pp. 20837-20856; Polyakov, I., Johnson, M.A., Arctic decadal and inter-decadal variability (2000) Geophys. Res. Lett., 27, pp. 4097-4100; Polyakov, I.V., Bekryaev, R.V., Alekseev, G.V., Bhatt, U., Colony, R.L., Johnson, M.A., Makshtas, A.P., Variability and trends of air temperature and pressure in the maritime Arctic, 1875-2000 (2002) J. Climate, , http://www.frontier.iarc.uaf.edu/~igor/sat_slp.pdf, submitted, (see); Polyakov, I.V., Alekseev, G.V., Bekryaev, R.V., Bhatt, U., Colony, R.L., Johnson, M.A., Karklin, V.P., Yulin, A.V., Long-term variability of ice in the arctic marginal seas (2002) J. Climate, , http://www.frontier.iarc.uaf.edu/~igor/ice.pdf, accepted, (see); Przybylak, R., Temporal and spatial variation of surface air temperature over the period of instrumental observations in the Arctic (2000) Int. J. Climattol., 20, pp. 587-614; Rigor, I.G., Colony, R.L., Martin, S., Variations in surface air temperature observations in the Arctic, 1979-1997 (2000) J. Climate, 13, pp. 896-914; Vinnikov, K.Ya., Gruza, G.V., Zakharov, V.F., Kirillov, A.A., Kovyneva, N.P., Ran'kova, E.Ya., Recent climatic changes in the Northern Hemisphere (1980) Soviet Meteorology and Hydrology, 6, pp. 1-10; Vinje, T., Anomalies and trends of sea-ice extent and atmospheric circulation in the Nordic Seas during the period 1864-1998 (2001) J. Climate, 14, pp. 255-267; Vinje, T., (2002) An Oscillation in the Barents Sea Climate System of Period 70 Years: Indication of a Colder Climate Ahead, , unpublished manuscript; Zubov, N.N., (1943) Arctic Ice, , Washington, U.S. Navy Electronics Laboratory, 491 pp. [NTIS: AD-426972]","Polyakov, I.V.; Int